Optional: Create a stereo image for viewing in 3D VR, using this custom node:
https://github.com/Dobidop/ComfyStereo

Scenes with objects that are too close might look really disorienting. Might be an issue of the depthmap not really being made for this projection. If anyone can find a better depthmap, please let me know.

Increasing divergence here will increase the 3D effect, but it looks okay at this default value and kind of weird if you increase it much more.
If you're using a 2x upscale model, you can skip the step that scales down by half. Not sure what the best upscale model to use here is, they kinda all look bad.
Connect latent here for txt2img vs img2img mode. For img2img, make sure the image sizes match what's in the loaded image. Change the first denoise to something below 1 for img2img.

Optional: Dev-to-Schnell LoRA https://civitai.com/models/686704/flux-dev-to-schnell-4-step-lora
This lets you use 4-8 steps and still get good results, though there will be some amount of quality loss tradeoff for the speed increase. If you're not using this, increase steps to 20-30. Using half as many steps on the fix sections seems to work well.

If the seam is too strong to get fixed by this step, try increasing the denoise. Some subjects will work better than others. Indoor scenes still are fairly likely to have unusual proportions and composition.
Ensure the aspect ratio is 2:1. Generating at 2048 x 1024 + upscale looks much better in VR if you have the patience for it, but 1408 x 704 isn't too bad!

Flux Equirectangular 360 Panorama Workflow
LoRA here: https://civitai.com/models/735980

Create 360 skyboxes or environments viewable in VR (optionally with 3D depthmaps)

Custom nodes used:

https://github.com/melMass/comfy_mtb (for transforming the image to do the seam fix)
https://github.com/kijai/ComfyUI-KJNodes (for creating a shape mask to inpaint the seam)
https://github.com/ltdrdata/ComfyUI-Impact-Pack (for Gaussian blurring the mask)
https://github.com/evanspearman/ComfyMath (not on the registry? for basic math...)
https://github.com/city96/ComfyUI-GGUF (optional, for GGUF model loading)
https://github.com/Fannovel16/comfyui_controlnet_aux (optional, for depthmap)
https://github.com/Dobidop/ComfyStereo (optional, for stereo generation)

Trigger phrase is "equirectangular 360 degree panorama."

Having different clip_l and t5xxl prompts isn't completely necessary, but using comma-separated phrases in the clip_l prompt and full sentences in the t5xxl prompt does seem to help a bit with Flux in general.
I've been using an LLM for prompt expansion.

Guidance 2.5 works well for realistic settings, but I haven't had any issues using higher values.

Feel free to replace this GGUF loader node with a standard Diffusion Model Loader node if you don't use GGUF.
https://github.com/city96/ComfyUI-GGUF
